OL,3,CBBC reporter tells court she took
OL,4,C'utmost care' with Adams allegation
OL,6,FWhen Mr Hogan put it to her that the
OL,7,FBBC's defence did not involve standing
OL,8,Fover the allegation, she said: "I'm
OL,9,Fhere to defend the journalism Mr
OL,10,FHogan, and the points of law that the
OL,11,Fcase is being defended are points of
OL,12,Flaw."
OL,14,FShe said that the claim was presented
OL,15,Fas an allegation in the programme and
OL,16,Fthat terms such as "Martin believes"
OL,17,Fand "Spotlight understands" are used.
OL,19,F"Any reasonable person watching the
OL,20,Fprogramme would know we are making an
OL,21,Fallegation."
